[John 5:31](../../../bib/kjv/joh005.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">joh 5:31</span></span>

witness

Compare ([Joh 8:14](../../../bib/kjv/joh008.htm#014).md). In ([Joh
5:31](../../../bib/kjv/joh005.htm#031).md).

Our Lord, defending His Messianic claims before Jews who denied those
claims, accepts the biblical rule of evidence, which required "two
witnesses"; ([Joh 8:17](../../../bib/kjv/joh008.htm#017).md); ([Num
35:30](../../../bib/kjv/num035.htm#030).md); ([Deu
17:6](../../../bib/kjv/deu017.htm#006).md). A paraphrase of verse ([Joh
5:31](../../../bib/kjv/joh005.htm#031).md) would be: "If I bear witness of
myself ye will say my witness is not true."

Compare ([Joh 8:14](../../../bib/kjv/joh008.htm#014).md).

